====Usage notes====
* Liberal parties in German-speaking Europe are associated with support for [[free market|free-market]] economy and [[w:Small government|small government]]. These parties most often represent the centre or even the centre-right of the political spectrum.
* Differences between the classical and modern definitions of the word "liberal" can sometimes lead to ambiguous interpretations of set phrases.  For example, if one were to say that a certain region had "liberal gun laws," this could validly be interpreted with two opposite meanings and would be better to specify more clearly in an unambiguous sentence, paragraph, or article.

